  "title": "HAIRSTYLIST",
  "description": "<p>The Hairstylist is responsible for providing professional hair care services, including hair cutting, styling, coloring, and treatments, to meet client preferences and salon standards. The role involves consulting with clients, maintaining hygiene and safety standards, and delivering high-quality customer service.</p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>Perform hair cutting, styling, washing, and blow-drying services</p><p>Provide hair coloring, highlighting, rebonding, perming, and hair treatment services</p><p>Consult with clients to understand their hairstyle and hair care needs</p><p>Recommend suitable hairstyles, hair products, and treatments</p><p>Maintain cleanliness and hygiene of tools, equipment, and work area</p><p>Ensure compliance with salon safety and health regulations</p><p>Handle customer inquiries and provide excellent customer service</p><p>Keep updated with latest hair styling trends and techniques</p><p>Required Skills</p><p>Strong knowledge of hair cutting and styling techniques</p><p>Experience in hair coloring and chemical treatments</p><p>Good communication and customer service skills</p><p>Ability to work independently and as part of a team</p><p>Time management and attention to detail</p><p>Knowledge of hygiene and safety standards</p><p>Qualifications</p><p>Certificate or diploma in Hairdressing or Cosmetology (preferred)</p><p>Relevant working experience as a Hairstylist</p>",
